    <div class="post-container" id="fpc-2789995">
                      
		<div class="post" id="post-2789995">
		<div class="long">
			<div class="head">
									<div class="options">
						<a href="javascript:;" onclick="togglePostFold(event,2789995)" class="btn btn-default btn-small btn-sm">Fold</a>
					</div>
								<div class="title" id="post-title-2789995">
																		
															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1956625&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227424" alt="DrChandra" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1956625)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;" >DrChandra</a></span> <span class="odate time_1491960614 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Apr 2017 01:30</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2789995">
									

<p>Yeah, the Circus does horrible stuff, even after Herman left. I don't think any of our GOIs are really innocent (Manna is only in it for the tax write offs), and I especially don't think the GOC is. The GOC wants to exterminate everything anomalous, and since nearly every other GOI benefits from anomalies in some way, it seems to me they'd be pretty unpopular. From Icky's point of view, freaks are Jews and the SCP and GOC are Nazis, so if they come onto her turf she'll go full inglorious bastards on them. I'm not saying that's objectively right, I'm just saying she see's herself as protecting freaks from those who would kill and imprison them. She's not punishing this guy so much as she's preventing him from reporting back to the GOC.</p>
<p>But I like the Circus so don't hold your breath on the comeuppance. Their Fortune Teller prevents them from being taken by surprise, the Kaleidoscope lets them escape to anywhere in the multiverse, and even if they did have to fight the Clowns would just take on their true monstrous forms and that MTF is up a creek. It's an Eldridtch circus, and the Foundation would be wise to just let them be. I might consider writing a tale about what Herman is up to these days if you're really itching for some justice. He's probably not doing too well since he got the boot.</p>
<p>To Random Day and anyone else who's offended by Jerry getting murdered, I apologize, but this tale was supposed to be darkly humorous. The Circus is a dark place beneath the candy coloured tents.</p>

							</div>

								
					
