					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1841781&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227424" alt="A Random Day" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1841781)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/a-random-day" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1841781); return false;" >A Random Day</a></span> <span class="odate time_1491961636 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Apr 2017 01:47</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2790005">
									

<p>Let me be clear about something - I'm not offended by Jerry getting murdered. I simply didn't enjoy reading about it. The humor failed miserably because I found it near impossible to sympathize with Icky or anyone else in the Circus. If anything, Jerry is the only relatable, sympathetic character in this story because he's a normal human.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>She's not punishing this guy so much as she's preventing him from reporting back to the GOC.</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>&quot;You just do recon? Every freak you ever ratted out to the Geo Sea is dead! They’re literal Nazis bent on wiping my kind from the Earth! This Circus is a sanctuary for freaks, which means there’s no way in hell you’re getting out alive.&quot;</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This is absolutely punishment. No matter how Icky sees it, this isn't Inglorious Basterds - it's <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Death_of_Andrew_Sadek">Andrew Sadek</a>.</p>

							</div>

								
