															</div>
				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1956625&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227424" alt="DrChandra" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1956625)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;" >DrChandra</a></span> <span class="odate time_1491973292 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">12 Apr 2017 05:01</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2790086">
									

<p>&quot;Also, I've always believed the Circus isn't the stereotypical evil chopper carnival but an actual entertainment group with (admittedly) a lot of weird stuff, who actually want to give people a good time.&quot;</p>
<p>Fully agree, and I think my portrayal of them in my previous tale might better depict that. Maybe give that a look over and let me know if you agree. If it makes you feel any better after this mini-fiasco I won't be depicting the Circus like this again.</p>
<p>First and foremost, the Circus (at least post Fuller) is a community of anomalous entities just trying to make a living and avoid the various MIBs, but because they do have enemies they will do what they have to to keep the Circus safe. In other tales and SCPs, Manny kills people (Dick C. Normous), punishes 'traitors' with torture (Tom) and kidnaps kids for his acts (according to Motormouth). Even in the Upside Down Face era, the Circus still does fucked up stuff and I believe it is fully in character for them to kill an enemy operative.</p>
<p>I'm sorry, I really didn't foresee this tale being so contentious. My beta readers loved it, and I really didn't foresee that having my killer clown believe she was acting in pre-emptive self-defence would offend anyone, and I did that precisely because she's not a psychotic killer clown but because she genuinely would do anything for the Circus.</p>
<p>I think I understand Random's point in that he empathizes more with Jerry than with Icky, but my sympathies lie with her and the Circus and I think it makes sense that a GOI devoted to protecting freaks would have a homicidal hatred of one dedicated to wiping them out. I still think it's possible to like this tale even if you view the Circus as the bad guys.</p>

							</div>

								
					
