			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-2790623">
									

<blockquote>
<p>I've always believed the Circus isn't the stereotypical evil chopper carnival but an actual entertainment group with (admittedly) a lot of weird stuff, who actually want to give people a good time.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Personally, I see them as in-between, like any other GOI- neither completely evil or completely innocent. On the one hand, they give a certain type of anomaly a place to belong, and do genuinely seek to entertain in their own way. On the other, they have a skewed &quot;cycle of abuse&quot; morality going on at several levels, and compound that with an us-vs-them mentality that lets them rationalize a lot of horrible acts in the name of self-preservation or &quot;helping&quot; others.</p>

