				<div class="info">
					<span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;"  ><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1956625&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1610227424" alt="DrChandra" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1956625)"/></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/drchandra" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1956625); return false;" >DrChandra</a></span> <span class="odate time_1535324922 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">26 Aug 2018 23:08</span>
														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3930630">
									

<p>Took me a minute to realize what you meant by Snow-to-Coin, but no. By most metrics, yes, Icky is better than Fuller, but that doesn't mean she's flawless. This was only the second entry in the series and I was still sorting out how I was portraying the Circus.</p>
<p>Bottomline, most people would agree that Icky really wasn't justified in killing this guy, and I'm fine with that. If you threaten anyone she cares about (as the GOC does), she goes full blown psycho Clown. As stated here and in <a href="/freaks-friends-and-fiends">Freaks Friends and Fiends</a>, Icky and Lolly (as well as other Circus members) regard the GOC as Nazis trying to exterminate them, and hate them with an intent fervour. And I fully acknowledge that it's debatable whether or not that hatred is justified.</p>

							</div>

								
					
